var title_f42_63_44028="Routine labs asymptomatic HIV";
var content_f42_63_44028=[" <div id=\"graphicsToolbar\">",
"  <div id=\"graphicsCopy\">",
"   &copy;2013 UpToDate",
"   <sup>",
"    &reg;",
"   </sup>",
"  </div>",
"  <div id=\"graphicsLinks\">",
"   <a href=\"?imageKey=ID%2F55701&amp;source=image_view&amp;view=print&amp;elapsedTimeMs=7\" onclick=\"\">",
"    <img alt=\"Print this page\" src=\"./../images/icn_print.myextg\" title=\"Print this page\"/>",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"icontxt textLink\" href=\"?imageKey=ID%2F55701&amp;source=image_view&amp;view=print&amp;elapsedTimeMs=7\" onclick=\"\" title=\"Print this page\">",
"    Print",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"etacLink\" href=\"#\">",
"    <img alt=\"Email graphic(s)\" src=\"./../images/icn_email.myextg\" title=\"Email graphic(s)\"/>",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"icontxt textLink etacLink\" href=\"#\" title=\"Email graphic(s)\">",
"    Email",
"   </a>",
"  </div>",
" </div>",
" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Routine laboratory tests in asymptomatic HIV-infected patients",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\">",
"    <table cellspacing=\"0\">",
"     <tr>",
"      <td class=\"subtitle1\">",
"       Test",
"      </td>",
"      <td class=\"subtitle1\">",
"       Cost*",
"      </td>",
"      <td class=\"subtitle1\">",
"       Recommended frequency and comment",
"      </td>",
"     </tr>",
"     <tr>",
"      <td>",
"       HIV serology",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       $30-60",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       Repeat test for patients with positive test results and: 1) no confirmation available; 2) denial of commonly accepted risk factors; 3) test done with techniques other than standard serology; and 4) other reason for concern. Repeat test for indeterminate results at 3-6 months.",
"      </td>",
"     </tr>",
"     <tr>",
"      <td>",
"       CBC",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       $6-8",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       Repeat at 3-6 months, more frequently for low values and with administration of marrow-toxic drugs.",
"      </td>",
"     </tr>",
"     <tr>",
"      <td>",
"       VDRL or RPR",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       $5-16",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       Repeat annually.",
"      </td>",
"     </tr>",
"     <tr>",
"      <td>",
"       CD4 cell count and percent",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       $60-90",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       Repeat every 3-4 months, and repeat for results that represent \"milestones\" for therapeutic decisions (antiretroviral therapy and prophylaxis for opportunistic pathogens), and with results that do not make sense. Routine testing when counts are &lt;50/mm",
"       <sup>",
"        3",
"       </sup>",
"       are of minimal use except for monitoring response to antiretroviral regimens.",
"      </td>",
"     </tr>",
"     <tr>",
"      <td>",
"       Chest x-ray",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       $40-140",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       Indicated for symptoms and signs suggesting pulmonary disease or newly detected positive PPD.",
"      </td>",
"     </tr>",
"     <tr>",
"      <td>",
"       Serum chemistries",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       $10-15",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       Repeat annually or more frequently in patients with abnormal results and with administration of hepatoxic or nephrotoxic drugs.",
"      </td>",
"     </tr>",
"     <tr>",
"      <td>",
"       Pap smear",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       $25-40",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       Repeat at six months and then annually if results are normal; some advocate Pap smear every 6 months if CD4 cell count is 500/mm3. Results reported as \"inadequate\" should be repeated. Refer to a gynecologist for results showing atypia or greater on the Bethesda scale.",
"      </td>",
"     </tr>",
"     <tr>",
"      <td>",
"       PPD skin test",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       $1",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       Repeat annually in previously negative patients who have substantial risk.",
"      </td>",
"     </tr>",
"     <tr>",
"      <td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"2\">",
"       Hepatitis serology",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       $10-15",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       Anti-HAV, anti-HBs or anti-HBc to screen for vaccine candidates",
"      </td>",
"     </tr>",
"     <tr>",
"      <td>",
"       $40-60",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       HBsAg or anti-HCV in those with abnormal liver functions tests",
"      </td>",
"     </tr>",
"     <tr>",
"      <td>",
"       Toxoplasmosis serology",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       $12-15",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       Screen all patients and repeat in seronegatives if: 1) CD4 count is &le;100 /mm",
"       <sup>",
"        3",
"       </sup>",
"       and patient does not take TMP-SMX for P. carinii prophylaxis, and 2) symptoms suggesting toxoplasmosis encephalitis. Agglutination assays for IgG are preferred. IgM is not useful.",
"      </td>",
"     </tr>",
"     <tr>",
"      <td>",
"       G-6-PD (optional)",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       $14-20",
"      </td>",
"      <td>",
"       Test: 1) All patients; 2) susceptible hosts: primarily men (X-linked) with the following ancestry: African-American, Italian, Sephardic Jew, Arabs, and those from India and SE Asia; 3) those receiving oxidant drugs, especially dapsone and primaquine; or 4) those with typical symptoms following recovery.",
"      </td>",
"     </tr>",
"    </table>",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"     * Common charges based upon a survey of five laboratories.",
"    </div>",
"    <div class=\"reference\">",
"     Data from Barlett JG. Medical Management of HIV Infection. Port City Press, Baltimore, MD 1988.",
"    </div>",
"   </div>",
"  </div>",
" </div>",
"</div>"].join("\n");
